All through the first 1/2 of this video, I was yelling "do you not know? these have been covered by multiple channels, they haven't designed a board etc, they are just old(er) GPU's with a hacked bios and cheap-o heatsink etc...

Then you mentioned the BIOS altering the RAM etc, I thought you might have got it..... but no, not quite xD

Generally, if you can identify what the card was originally (manufacturer/model) then you can use that and nVFlash to 'fix' the bios - this generally works, they are usually a 5xx-7xx series card!

Other channels have done this, and fixed the cards ;) - come on LTT, You can usually do better than this xD
